conditional Statement or control statement:
-------------------------------------------
1)conditional statement
  i)if statement
     1.simple if 
	 2.if-else
	 3.ladder if
	 4.nested if
  ii)switch statement
------------------------------------------  
2)looping or interation Statement
  i)Entry control loop
     1.for loop
	 2.while loop
  ii)Exit control loop
     1.do-while loop
------------------------------------------	 
3)Branching or transfer statement
  i)break
  ii)continue
  iii)goto
------------------------------------------  
1)Simple if statement:
    It is used when you have only one condition,and a nmber of lines has to execute only
	if given condition is true.
	
	Syntax:
	 if(condition)
	 {
	    //if block;
	 }
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
WAP to calculate percentage of by accepting the three subject marks.
#include<stdio.h>
#include<conio.h>
void main()
{
   int sub1,sub2,sub3;
   float per;
   printf("Enter your three subject marks:");
   scanf("%d%d%d",&sub1,&sub2,&sub3);
   per=((sub1+sub2+sub3)*100)/300;
   printf("Your Percentage is=%f",per);
   getch();
   
}
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------	
if-else statement:
if-else statement is used when only one condition is given,but you have to execute 
different statement when condition is true or condition is false.

In if-else statement,if given condition is true then block of if will execute,
other wise else block is execute.

Syntax:
if(condition)
{
   //true_statement
}
else
{
   //false_statement
}
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
else-if ladder:
else-if ladder statement is used to when multiple condition is given but only one condition 
will execute at one time,then else-if ladder is used.

Syntax:
if(condition1)
{
   //statement
}
else if(condition2)
{
    //statement
}
..............
...............
................
else
{
   //statement
}  



























































	
	
	
	
	
	
	
	
	
	
	
	
	
	
	
	